{
  "generated_at": "2026-05-21",
  "context": "Three exploratory scene designs informed by Aubrey's AAC layout (persistent core columns + top-row category nav) and our coverage baseline. Proposal 1 was revised to v2 after recognizing that our SentenceEngine subsumes most grammatical glue.",
  "proposals": [
    {
      "name": "Core-First Home (Aubrey pattern, v2)",
      "description": "High-reach home modelled on Aubrey's AAC layout, with one critical adjustment: since our SentenceEngine assembles grammar automatically, we omit articles, conjunctions, copula, and modals from the tile set. We keep only tiles that change meaning the AI cannot infer \u2014 prepositions, demonstratives, pronouns (ownership/recipient), and the 'all_done' state.",
      "homePageKey": "home",
      "analysis_v2": {
        "principle": "Tile vocabulary must justify itself against the LLM's ability to fill grammatical glue. A tile only earns a slot on home if tapping it changes meaning the AI cannot infer from the rest of the tapped tiles.",
        "kept_classes": {
          "prepositions": "Change spatial meaning ('ball IN' vs 'ball OUT' vs 'ball ON').",
          "demonstratives": "Quantify/specify ('MORE cookie' vs 'cookie'; 'ALL done').",
          "state": "Convey utterance-level intent ('all_done' = I'm finished, not just 'done').",
          "pronouns": "Disambiguate ownership/recipient. 'MOM EAT MY COOKIE' vs 'MOM EAT YOUR COOKIE' is a meaning the AI cannot infer from context alone."
        },
        "dropped_groups": {
          "group_a_ai_fills_these": {
            "keys": [
              "a",
              "the",
              "and",
              "of",
              "to",
              "is",
              "can",
              "do"
            ],
            "rationale": "SentenceEngine inserts these for free. Child taps DAD WATER FRIES; AI generates 'Daddy, can I have water and fries?'. 'to' is the same \u2014 child taps GO SCHOOL; AI generates 'Let's go to school'. Putting these on home wastes real estate."
          },
          "group_b_misclassified_or_ui_controls": {
            "keys": [
              "clear",
              "extra_words",
              "abc_123",
              "blanket",
              "time"
            ],
            "rationale": "clear = tray-clear control (already implemented); extra_words = overflow nav (not a sentence tile); abc_123 = Aubrey's spelling-keyboard tile, we don't have spelling; blanket = ordinary content noun (belongs in vocab as a regular object tile, not grammar); time = ambiguous (question-word or noun), defer until concrete use."
          }
        },
        "implication_for_layout": "Removing the 13 dropped slots from a 60-tile Aubrey-style layout leaves ~47 useful tiles. The MVP we build first is a 24-tile home (6 categories + 6 pronouns + 6 verbs + 6 modifiers/states) that demonstrates the pattern; we grow from there."
      },
      "design_notes": [
        "Layout intent: 10 cols x 6 rows = 60 cells, but v2 leaves 13 cells empty or reflows to ~48.",
        "Aubrey's drinks-page pattern (sibling-category strip + persistent left core column) is the load-bearing UX move; ship the home first, then evaluate schema evolution to support it cleanly.",
        "Blocked by 18 missing vocabulary keys \u2014 see vocabulary_additions_required."
      ],
